---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Best Words for Premium Squares in Scrabble — Maximize DL, TL, DW, TW"
  description="Which words to aim for when you have access to premium squares. High-value letters on TLS, short words on TWS, and the math behind each scoring opportunity."
  keywords="premium squares scrabble, triple word score words, double letter words, scrabble scoring strategy, best words for TLS, TW square strategy, premium square targets"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best Words for Premium Squares in Scrabble — Maximize DL, TL, DW, TW",
    "description": "Which words to aim for when you have access to premium squares. High-value letters on TLS, short words on TWS, and the math behind each scoring opportunity.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/best-words-for-premium-squares" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best letters to place on Triple Letter squares?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Z (10pts → 30pts), Q (10pts → 30pts), X (8pts → 24pts), and J (8pts → 24pts) gain the most from Triple Letter squares. Even mid-value tiles like K (5pts → 15pts) and V (4pts → 12pts) are strong TLS targets. Low-value tiles like E or A waste the multiplier." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I play short or long words on Triple Word squares?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Both work, but for different reasons. Short words (3-4 letters) with high-value tiles on adjacent letter multipliers can score 60-80 points. Long words (6-7 letters) on TWS score through volume — even common letters add up when tripled. Bingos through TWS are the ultimate play (word ×3 plus 50-point bonus)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you combine letter and word multipliers in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Letter multipliers (DLS, TLS) apply first to individual tiles. Then the word total — including those boosted tiles — gets multiplied by word multipliers (DWS, TWS). So a Z on TLS within a TWS word scores 10×3 = 30 for the Z, then the whole word including that 30 is tripled. The Z alone contributes 90 effective points." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Strategy</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best Words for Premium Squares — Maximize Every Multiplier</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Knowing a word is valid is step one. Knowing where to place it is where the real points live. Premium squares can turn a 12-point play into a 60-point play — but only if you're targeting them with the right tiles. Here's how to choose words that extract maximum value from every DL, TL, DW, and TW on the board.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card: TWS = Highest Value -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Highest Value</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">TWS + TLS COMBO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">A single tile can contribute 90 effective points — Z on TLS within a TWS word = 10×3×3</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The most powerful scoring opportunity in Scrabble isn't a long word or a rare word — it's placing a high-value tile on a letter multiplier inside a word that also hits a word multiplier. Two multipliers, one turn, devastating results.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How Each Premium Square Type Works</h2>

      <p>Before choosing target words, understand what each multiplier does and when it fires. Letter multipliers boost one tile; word multipliers boost the final sum. They stack when combined.</p>

      <!-- Table: Premium Square Types -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Square</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Multiplier</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Count</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Best Targets</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">DLS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">×2 one tile</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">J, X, Z, Q, K — mid-high tiles</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">TLS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">×3 one tile</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Z, Q (30pts), X, J (24pts)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-pink-400">DWS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">×2 whole word</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Long words, bingos, high base totals</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-red-400">TWS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">×3 whole word</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Any word with combined letter bonuses</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip: Multiplication Math -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DLS tile gain</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TLS tile gain</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TLS + DWS combo</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TLS + TWS combo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Best Letters for Each Square Type</h2>

      <p>Not all tiles benefit equally from multipliers. Putting an E on TLS gains you 2 extra points. Putting a Z there gains 20. Here's the priority for each square type.</p>

      <!-- Card Grid: Strategy per Square -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟦 DLS Targets</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Z (10→20), Q (10→20), X (8→16), J (8→16), K (5→10). Even H (4→8) and V (4→8) are solid. Skip vowels on DLS — the gain is negligible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟫 TLS Targets</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Z/Q (10→30), X/J (8→24), K (5→15). A single Z on TLS outscores most 4-letter words. This is the highest-impact letter multiplier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-pink-500/30 bg-pink-950/10">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟪 DWS Targets</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Long words with multiple consonants. QUARTZ (24×2=48), JINXED (21×2=42). Every tile benefits — length matters more than individual tile value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟥 TWS Targets</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Anything that also hits a letter multiplier. ZONE with Z on TLS through TWS = (30+1+1+1)×3 = 99 pts. Short words with one power tile dominate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Golden Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">For letter multipliers (DLS/TLS): prioritize <span class="text-white font-medium">tile value</span> — place your most expensive letter on the bonus. For word multipliers (DWS/TWS): prioritize <span class="text-white font-medium">total word score</span> — make the base sum as high as possible before the multiplier kicks in.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Optimal Word Length by Square Type</h2>

      <p>Word length interacts with multiplier type in ways many players overlook. Short words can outscore long ones when placed correctly.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Short Words + TWS</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZAX (19×3=57), QI with Q on TLS (31×3=93). Short words reach TWS corners more easily and still score huge when a power tile hits a letter multiplier in the same play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Long Words + DWS</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUIXOTE (23×2=46+50=96 with bingo). DWS rewards volume — every tile in a 7-letter word gets doubled. Length + bingo + DWS = devastating.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Numbered Steps: Scoring Examples with Math -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Scoring Examples — The Math</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">ZAP</span> with Z on TLS, word on TWS: (10×3)+1+3 = 34, ×3 = <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold">102 pts</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">JINX</span> with J on DLS, word on DWS: (8×2)+1+1+8 = 26, ×2 = <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold">52 pts</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">QUIZ</span> with Q on TLS, word on DWS: (10×3)+1+1+10 = 42, ×2 = <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold">84 pts</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">WAXEN</span> (bingo through existing A) on TWS: (4+1+8+1+1)×3+50 = <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold">95 pts</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Dig Deeper Cross-Link -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/understanding-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Understanding Premium Squares — full board layout and one-turn rule explained</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scoring-100-points-single-turn/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Scoring 100+ Points in a Single Turn — bingos, multiplier stacking, and real examples</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Offensive vs Defensive Premium Play</h2>

      <p>Premium squares are a double-edged sword. Every time you reach for one, you might be opening another for your opponent. The best players weigh the trade-off on every turn.</p>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Offensive Plays</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Target TWS with power tiles. Extend through multiple premiums. Play bingos that land on word multipliers. Sacrifice safety for 50+ point swings when ahead.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Risky Plays to Avoid</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Playing adjacent to open TWS without using it. Leaving vowels next to TLS for opponent's Q/Z. Opening TWS lanes when opponent holds power tiles. Short plays that enable longer extensions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Purple Strategy Tiles: When to Target vs Avoid -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target aggressively when:</span> You hold Z/Q/X/J and a TLS is reachable. You have a bingo aimed at TWS. You're behind and need a swing play. Your opponent's rack is weak (they exchanged tiles recently).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play defensively when:</span> You're ahead — protect the lead. The only path to TWS opens a parallel TLS for your opponent. You don't have high-value tiles to justify the risk. Late game when tile tracking shows opponent holds power tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Block rather than score when:</span> Opponent is building toward a TWS lane. A cheap 2-letter word can neutralize a dangerous square permanently. You can cover a TLS with a low-value tile that denies the opponent 20+ points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Decision Framework</h2>

      <p>Use this mental checklist every time you see a premium square opportunity. It takes seconds but prevents costly mistakes.</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps: Decision Framework -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Decision Checklist</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Identify:</span> Which premium squares can I reach this turn? TLS near my high-value tile? TWS at the end of a lane?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Calculate:</span> What's the score WITH the multiplier vs my best play WITHOUT? Is the multiplier adding 20+ points?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Assess risk:</span> Does my play open a bigger premium for my opponent? What's the worst they can score from what I leave exposed?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Compare net gain:</span> My score minus their likely reply. If the net is positive by 15+, take the premium. If it's breakeven or worse, play safe.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">5</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Rack leave:</span> Does targeting this premium force me to keep bad tiles? A 50-point play that leaves UUIIV is worse than a 35-point play that keeps STEIN.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words — All-Time Records & Analysis</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/blocking-triple-word-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Blocking Triple Word Squares — Defensive Scrabble Strategy</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/how-to-play-around-triple-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">How to Play Around Triple Word Squares — Lane Control</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA Box -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-indigo-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find your highest-scoring words — free, instant, no signup needed</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
